<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Future Improvements</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }
        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #687d8f 0%, #778b9c 100%);
            min-height: 100vh;
        }
        nav {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
            backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
            padding: 1rem 2rem;
        }
        nav ul {
            list-style: none;
            display: flex;
            gap: 2rem;
            justify-content: center;
        }
        nav a {
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 500;
            transition: opacity 0.3s;
        }
        nav a:hover {
            opacity: 0.8;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 4rem auto;
            padding: 2rem;
        }
        .content-card {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 20px;
            padding: 3rem;
            box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: #697e90;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
        .subtitle {
            color: #999;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            font-style: italic;
        }
        h2 {
            color: #697e90;
            margin-top: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            font-size: 1.5rem;
        }
        p {
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            color: #555;
        }
        .improvement-list {
            list-style: none;
            margin-top: 2rem;
        }
        .improvement-item {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8f7f5 0%, rgba(118, 75, 162, 0.05) 100%);
            border-left: 5px solid #697e90;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: transform 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
        }
        .improvement-item:hover {
            transform: translateX(5px);
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.15);
        }
        .improvement-title {
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: #697e90;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
        .improvement-description {
            color: #666;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .status-badge {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
            background: #778b9c;
            color: white;
            border-radius: 15px;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            margin-top: 0.5rem;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <nav>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
            <li><a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a></li>
            <li><a href="/future-improvements">Future Improvements</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="content-card">
            <h1>Future Improvements</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Exciting features we're planning to add to Mile Square Sweeping</p>

            <p>We're constantly working to improve your experience with Mile Square Sweeping. Here's what we have planned for the future:</p>

            <ul class="improvement-list">
                <li class="improvement-item">
                    <div class="improvement-title">Move your car alerts</div>
                    <div class="improvement-description">
                        With one click of a button, add a local notification to be reminded when to move your car. Can be customized to remind you when you want.
                    </div>
                    <span class="status-badge">In Development</span>
                </li>
                <li class="improvement-item">
                    <div class="improvement-title">Street Closures</div>
                    <div class="improvement-description">
                        Stay informed about temporary street closures due to events, construction, or emergencies. We'll integrate real-time street closure data so you can plan your parking and routes accordingly. Get notifications about closures near your saved locations.
                    </div>
                    <span class="status-badge">In Development</span>
                </li>

                <li class="improvement-item">
                    <div class="improvement-title">Pay Parking Identification</div>
                    <div class="improvement-description">
                        Find all parking garages and which streets are pay parking only.
                    </div>
                    <span class="status-badge">Planned</span>
                </li>

                <li class="improvement-item">
                    <div class="improvement-title">Temporary No Parking</div>
                    <div class="improvement-description">
                        Show the spots that have temporary no parking upcoming.
                    </div>
                    <span class="status-badge">Planned</span>
                </li>

                <li class="improvement-item">
                    <div class="improvement-title">Android App</div>
                    <div class="improvement-description">
                        Everything from the iOS app but on your Android device
                    </div>
                    <span class="status-badge">Planned</span>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Have a Suggestion?</h2>
            <p>We'd love to hear your ideas! If you have a feature request or suggestion for improving Mile Square Sweeping, please <a href="/contact" style="color: #667eea; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600;">get in touch</a> with us.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
